1 Solea creder lo mondo in suo periclo 2 che la bella Ciprigna il folle amore 3 raggiasse, volta nel terzo epiciclo;
4 per che non pur a lei faceano onore 5 di sacrificio e di votivo grido 6 le genti antiche ne l’antico errore;
7 ma Dïone onoravano e Cupido, 8 quella per madre sua, questo per figlio, 9 e dicean ch’el sedette in grembo a Dido;
10 e da costei ond’ io principio piglio 11 pigliavano il vocabol de la stella 12 che ’l sol vagheggia or da coppa or da ciglio.

query.result:
**English:**
1 The world used to believe, to its peril, 2 that beautiful Venus, the mad love, 3 shone, turned in the third epicycle;
4 because of which the ancient people, in their ancient error, 5 not only paid her honor 6 with sacrifices and votive cries;
7 but they also honored Dione and Cupid, 8 she as his mother, he as her son, 9 and they said that he sat in Dido's lap;
10 and from her, from whom I take my beginning, 11 they took the name of the star 12 that the sun courts now from above, now from below.
**Sanskrit:**
1 Loko viśvasya bhayena manyate sma 2 śubhāṃ śukrāṃ vikṣiptaṃ ratiṃ kāmam 3 bhramantīm tṛtīye paridhi;
4 yasmāt na kevalam tasyai pūjāṃ kurvanti sma 5 yajñena ca prārthanāśabdena ca 6 pūrve janāḥ pūrve mohe;
7 api tu Dyonīm ca Kāmam ca pūjayanti sma, 8 tām mātṛtvena enam putratvena, 9 āhuś ca enam Didoḥ aṅke nīvīte upaviṣṭam;
10 tasyāś ca yataḥ aham ārabhe 11 tārāyā nāma gṛhṇanti sma 12 yāṃ sūryaḥ abhilāṣate adhastād vā upari vā.

